        "Approved false (USE) Operating Budget Template 318000.0 0 318000.0 Despite being a small, three person team, the department continues to deliver a high level of service and support to veterans and their families across the county. Over the last calendar year, the department accomplished more than 1,750 documented actions in direct support of local veterans and their families. In terms of client interactions, the team managed â€¢ 1,143 in person appointments â€¢ 4,695 phone consultations This level of service reflects the departmentâ€™s commitment, efficiency, and dedication to meeting the needs of the veteran community, often exceeding expectations given the limited staffing and resources. One of the departmentâ€™s most significant challenges remains public awareness. While the department enjoys an excellent reputation within the community, that recognition is often limited to those who have had direct interactions or heard through word of mouth. Outside of a few publications and social media platforms, our outreach efforts are minimal. To truly showcase the departmentâ€™s capabilities and the value we bring to the community, we must consistently seek new and creative ways to elevate our visibility. Expanding our communication strategies, leveraging partnerships, and enhancing our presence in both digital and in person spaces will be essential for strengthening public engagement and fostering greater awareness of our mission and impact. The Veteran Services Department wants to communicate with every veteran and his/her dependents in Walton County, to administer and advocate for all the benefits they have earned. To provide excellent customer service for all our veterans and family members in such a manner that depicts the gratitude and honor reserved for those who have sacrificed so much. We believe the best way to represent the Board of County Commissioners and instill confidence in local government is to provide accurate information and serve our clients in a courteous and professional manner. Maintain the highest caliber of educated and empathetic staff in the area of veteran services. Coordinate with other veteran service organizations, both public and private to adopt best practices and garner resources for Walton County veterans and their families. Develop and maintain a professional atmosphere consistent with Walton County values and the pledge given to those who serve and their families. Educate the veterans and family members of Walton County on the benefits/resources at the federal, state and local level in order to assist them in achieving and maintaining the highest quality of life. Advocate for those we serve to the Department of Veteran Affairs, Florida Department of Veteran Affairs and Board of County Commissioners, for entitled benefits and resources needed. To strengthen community ties and expand the departmentâ€™s visibility, we are setting clear, measurable goals for the upcoming fiscal and calendar years",
        "Increase Public Engagement Opportunities by 50%",
        "Last fiscal year, the department participated in five publicized community events. This year, we will increase our involvement to eight events across the county, ensuring greater access and visibility in diverse areas.",
