    "public-defender": {
      "department": "Public Defender",
      "serviceArea": "Judicial & Statutory Services",
      "description": "Approved true Basic 737380.0 200000.0 537380.0 When counties are responsible for court technology costs as specified in Section 29.008(1)(f)2. and (h), an allocation of $2 will be made to the county board of commissioners. This amount is dedicated solely to funding court related technology, supporting the technology needs of state trial courts, state attorneys, public defenders, and criminal conflict and civil regional counsel within the county, as defined in the same section.",
      "services": [
        "Public Defender",
        "Approved true (USE) Operating Budget Template 372000.0 215000.0 157000.0 Our department's function fulfills a vital role in collaborating with the judicial system to enforce court ordered obligations for probationers sentenced to county probation. The probation department monitors the progress of probationers to ensure compliance with the various court ordered conditions. The objective is to effectively manage and operate a professional, cost efficient Probation Office, with the aim of enhancing public relations, fostering a more service and solution oriented government, and cultivating trust in the County Government. Our commitment includes the endeavor to minimize office expenditures while upholding optimal performance and integrity. We are requesting an increase in Other Services to cover the cost of our renewal fee for Tyler Supervision. At this time, our office does not plan to purchase any machinery or equipment. The Walton County Probation Office fulfills a vital role in collaborating with the judicial system to enforce court ordered obligations for probationers sentenced in the County court, as well as cases that have been reduced to misdemeanors from the Felony court. The dedicated Probation Officers within the office diligently monitor the progress of probationers, ensuring compliance with the various court ordered conditions. These conditions encompass a wide range of requirements, including community service, completion of DUI school, Anger Management and Batterer's Intervention programs, obtaining a valid driver's license, attending counseling sessions for substance abuse and psychological matters, engaging in alcohol anonymous meetings, vehicle immobilization, making payments for fines, costs, fees, and restitution, and undergoing random urinalysis testing, among other possible obligations. Maintaining effective collaboration with agencies such as the Judicial office, State Attorney, Public Defenders, private attorneys, community organizations, and counselors is of utmost importance. This collaborative effort ensures that probationers receive clear instructions and guidance to successfully fulfill the terms of their probation. Through commitment and coordination, the Walton County Probation Office strives to support rehabilitation and successful completion of probation for individuals within the community, promoting accountability and adherence to court ordered requirements. At this time, we do not anticipate any staffing changes.",
        "Approved true Basic 36000.0 0 36000.0 The Public Defender represents any person who is determined by the Court to be indigent, as provided in Section 27.52, Florida Statutes, and who is charged with a felony or criminal misdemeanor, or as a delinquent child, pursuant to a petition filed before a circuit court, Baker Act, and any other person the Court may designate. Pursuant to Florida Statute 27.54, the County shall provide this office with office space, utilities, telephone services, custodial services, library services, transportation services, communications services and payment of pretrial costs. Walton County provides its share of these costs along with the other counties of the 1st Judicial Circuit."
      ],
      "capitalProjects": [],
      "performanceMeasures": [
        "Approved true (USE) Operating Budget Template 372000.0 215000.0 157000.0 Our department's function fulfills a vital role in collaborating with the judicial system to enforce court ordered obligations for probationers sentenced to county probation. The probation department monitors the progress of probationers to ensure compliance with the various court ordered conditions. The objective is to effectively manage and operate a professional, cost efficient Probation Office, with the aim of enhancing public relations, fostering a more service and solution oriented government, and cultivating trust in the County Government. Our commitment includes the endeavor to minimize office expenditures while upholding optimal performance and integrity. We are requesting an increase in Other Services to cover the cost of our renewal fee for Tyler Supervision. At this time, our office does not plan to purchase any machinery or equipment. The Walton County Probation Office fulfills a vital role in collaborating with the judicial system to enforce court ordered obligations for probationers sentenced in the County court, as well as cases that have been reduced to misdemeanors from the Felony court. The dedicated Probation Officers within the office diligently monitor the progress of probationers, ensuring compliance with the various court ordered conditions. These conditions encompass a wide range of requirements, including community service, completion of DUI school, Anger Management and Batterer's Intervention programs, obtaining a valid driver's license, attending counseling sessions for substance abuse and psychological matters, engaging in alcohol anonymous meetings, vehicle immobilization, making payments for fines, costs, fees, and restitution, and undergoing random urinalysis testing, among other possible obligations. Maintaining effective collaboration with agencies such as the Judicial office, State Attorney, Public Defenders, private attorneys, community organizations, and counselors is of utmost importance. This collaborative effort ensures that probationers receive clear instructions and guidance to successfully fulfill the terms of their probation. Through commitment and coordination, the Walton County Probation Office strives to support rehabilitation and successful completion of probation for individuals within the community, promoting accountability and adherence to court ordered requirements. At this time, we do not anticipate any staffing changes."
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
