      "description": "Approved true (USE) Operating Budget Template 598000.0 0 598000.0 The Walton County Extension Service (also known as Agricultural Extension Services) provides scientifically based information for current and pertinent issues that will enable county residents and non residents to make informed decisions that will improve their quality of life. Access of such knowledge is available from the University of Florida and is provided by trained professionals (extension agents). Development of educational programs takes into consideration changes that affect Walton County government, its residents, the environment, and natural and human resources. Local extension education programs are cooperatively funded by the County, the University of Florida, the U.S. Department of Agriculture, and other joint cooperators. The Walton County Extension Service aims to provide scientifically based educational programs and resources that empower residents to make informed decisions about agriculture, horticulture, natural resources, forestry, family and consumer science and youth development. By delivering high quality, research driven knowledge, the Extension Service seeks to enhance the quality of life for both residents and non residents of Walton County, promote environmental stewardship, and support sustainable economic growth. The proposed budget maintains funds. Yes Requesting a 2026 Nissan Frontier 4X4 crew cab truck (not to exceed $40,000) to replace the 2005 Ford F150. Per the advice of Justin Missildine, Fleet Manager the 2005 Ford F150 was sent surplus due to repair needs exceeding the value of the truck. The twenty one year old truck had a bad instrument panel and needed a new transmission. Because of the vehicle's age, parts were obsolete and surplus was recommended. Justin was consulted and constructed a quote for an appropriate replacement vehicle for our department. Currently we are borrowing a truck when needed. Value ($202,634) and number of donated volunteer hours (7100 hours) Additional external grant and in kind funding ($115,975) Number of educational events (342 events) for adult and youth participants (8787 participants) Individual field visits (163) Phone calls (1026) Office consultations (602) Emails (1943) Text (256) Website visits (360,281) Social Media Reach (58,438) Total Master Gardener Volunteers (61) Salaries and wages were reduced during the 2025 20226 fiscal year as Dr. Laura Tiu accepted a new position. Amanda Masholie was appointed Interim County Extension Director (CED) with UF paying the Interim CED stipend beginning in December. Further Ian Stone resigned from his position effective March 20, 2026.",
      "services": [
        "Approved true (USE) Operating Budget Template 598000.0 0 598000.0 The Walton County Extension Service (also known as Agricultural Extension Services) provides scientifically based information for current and pertinent issues that will enable county residents and non residents to make informed decisions that will improve their quality of life. Access of such knowledge is available from the University of Florida and is provided by trained professionals (extension agents). Development of educational programs takes into consideration changes that affect Walton County government, its residents, the environment, and natural and human resources. Local extension education programs are cooperatively funded by the County, the University of Florida, the U.S. Department of Agriculture, and other joint cooperators. The Walton County Extension Service aims to provide scientifically based educational programs and resources that empower residents to make informed decisions about agriculture, horticulture, natural resources, forestry, family and consumer science and youth development. By delivering high quality, research driven knowledge, the Extension Service seeks to enhance the quality of life for both residents and non residents of Walton County, promote environmental stewardship, and support sustainable economic growth. The proposed budget maintains funds. Yes Requesting a 2026 Nissan Frontier 4X4 crew cab truck (not to exceed $40,000) to replace the 2005 Ford F150. Per the advice of Justin Missildine, Fleet Manager the 2005 Ford F150 was sent surplus due to repair needs exceeding the value of the truck. The twenty one year old truck had a bad instrument panel and needed a new transmission. Because of the vehicle's age, parts were obsolete and surplus was recommended. Justin was consulted and constructed a quote for an appropriate replacement vehicle for our department. Currently we are borrowing a truck when needed. Value ($202,634) and number of donated volunteer hours (7100 hours) Additional external grant and in kind funding ($115,975) Number of educational events (342 events) for adult and youth participants (8787 participants) Individual field visits (163) Phone calls (1026) Office consultations (602) Emails (1943) Text (256) Website visits (360,281) Social Media Reach (58,438) Total Master Gardener Volunteers (61) Salaries and wages were reduced during the 2025 20226 fiscal year as Dr. Laura Tiu accepted a new position. Amanda Masholie was appointed Interim County Extension Director (CED) with UF paying the Interim CED stipend beginning in December. Further Ian Stone resigned from his position effective March 20, 2026."
      ],
