      "description": "State Attorney Facility | Approved | true | Basic | 25000.0 | 0 | -25000.0 | The State Attorney is elected for each judicial circuit. The officeâ€™s responsibilities include appearing in the circuit and County courts within its judicial circuit and prosecuting or defending on behalf of the State all suits, applications, or motions, civil or criminal, in which the State is a party. Other duties involve attending grand jury sessions when required, summoning and examining witnesses for the State and assisting the State Attorney General on appeals from its respective circuit to the Supreme Court. Pursuant to Florida Statute 27.34, the County shall provide this office with office space, utilities, telephone services, custodial services, library services, transportation services and communications services. Walton County provides its share of these costs along with the other counties within the 1st Judicial Circuit.",
